cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it proposes a pruning algorithm for models and evaluates its performance on image classification tasks. It also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) as it deals with pre-training of models and decision-making in pruning algorithms. Additionally, it may fall under the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category as it involves compressing and accelerating models in the training stage.
